1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,680
<i>We'll never be able to kill them all</i>

2
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,840
<i>as long as Phraya Kaipetch is still alive.</i>

3
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,680
Working together to eliminate Petch
is more important.

4
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,480
I want you to join me.

5
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,960
I won't be a pawn
in your revenge ever again.

6
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:16,200
You'll regret this, Lasor.

7
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,160
Yiam used the heart-twisting spell on you,

8
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,760
Yiwha was affected too.

9
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,960
<i>I won't ever do that again.</i>

10
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:25,280
<i>Please don't leave me.</i>

11
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:27,520
<i>If you love me this much,</i>

12
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,760
<i>how could I ever leave you?</i>

13
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:32,600
<i>I'll have you ordained</i>
<i>and send you to Lanka.</i>

14
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,160
It was all the work of those rebels

15
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:37,600
trying to strip me
of my position as governor, sir.

16
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:42,920
Pun,

17
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:45,200
what was that we just saw?

18
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,760
That Phraya Kaipetch bastard

19
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,880
unleashed black magic on the townspeople.
People died everywhere.

20
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,520
He's far more brutal
than we ever imagined.

21
00:02:59,000 --> 00:02:59,840
Dad!

22
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:06,840
At last,

23
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:10,280
Phraya Kaipetch
has revealed his true nature.

24
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,800
The townspeople must be terrified now.

25
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:16,160
No one will dare stand up to him anymore.

26
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:19,600
Only Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet

27
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:21,960
can be our hope now.

28
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:24,160
Petch will never allow
the High Commissioner

29
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:26,600
to see how ruined Tha Khiri has become.

30
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:30,080
Tomorrow night, all of us

31
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,520
must protect the High Commissioner.

32
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,560
We cannot let them harm him.

33
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:40,000
Chang,

34
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:41,960
where's Talong?

35
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,480
Pun told me about Talong.

36
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,000
I'm…

37
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,600
so sorry.

38
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,960
Talong loved me so much

39
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:28,800
that he was willing to die in my place.

40
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,680
But do you know…

41
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,120
I never even told him I loved him.

42
00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:48,280
I believe Talong knew how you felt.

43
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:51,840
And he'll always remain in your heart.

44
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,880
Maybe…

45
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:58,840
I believe
Talong is waiting for me somewhere.

46
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,280
I want to be with him.

47
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:15,320
Talong sacrificed his life for you.

48
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:20,080
That means he wanted you to keep living.

49
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:25,120
You must protect your life

50
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,280
because that's the final gift
Talong gave you.

51
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,640
I'll live for you, Talong.

52
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,040
Are you thinking about that young lady?

53
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,120
Lady Duen is my first

54
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,200
and only love.

55
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,680
Even if I were to see her again someday,

56
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,800
I probably wouldn't remember her anymore.

57
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:27,800
Between remembering

58
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,320
and forgetting, which one

59
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,840
do you think is more painful?

60
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,920
I don't know, Dad.

61
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,920
I've never forgotten anything.

62
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,880
For the past 25 years,

63
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,560
there hasn't been a single day
I haven't thought about Panan, your mom.

64
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,640
Because I never forgot,

65
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:06,840
I had to endure the agony
of losing the one I loved,

66
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,280
until I became a man without a heart.

67
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:16,920
Perhaps

68
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,120
having no memories left at all

69
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,160
might hurt less.

70
00:07:32,440 --> 00:07:33,480
So that's why

71
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,200
you want to erase my memories.

72
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,840
So I can finally escape
the hell inside my heart.

73
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,920
I understand now, Dad.

74
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,400
I really do.

75
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,760
From now on,

76
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,160
I'll leave the past behind

77
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:06,920
and prepare to become a new person

78
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,760
for you.

79
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,720
<i>Om, awaken the great power.</i>

80
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:26,840
<i>I awaken these armbands and talismans,</i>
<i>granting endurance and invulnerability.</i>

81
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:29,160
<i>I awaken Lek Lai metal</i>

82
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:32,520
<i>and copper</i>
<i>with sacred spells and supreme sorcery.</i>

83
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:36,320
<i>I awaken stone cliffs and ivory fangs.</i>
<i>I awaken spears,</i>

84
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,600
<i>halberds, swords,</i>
<i>bows, blades, and machetes.</i>

85
00:08:39,679 --> 00:08:44,039
<i>I awaken all manner of weapons,</i>
<i>turning them into royal swords of victory.</i>

86
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:50,480
<i>Rise and serve the royal command.</i>

87
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:53,760
<i>Sawaha, Sawahom…</i>

88
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,320
Take these armbands

89
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,480
and give them to every one of your men.

90
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:19,760
And these swords,
each one has been enchanted by me.

91
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:24,960
Take them.

92
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:26,200
Take these swords.

93
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:28,480
Listen carefully.

94
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:31,480
Go and bring me

95
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:33,720
the head

96
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:36,200
of Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet.

97
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,720
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

98
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,160
- Bandits!
- Protect the High Commissioner!

99
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:19,920
Run, sir.

100
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,080
Please run, sir.

101
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:03,080
<i>Na kluean, mo thon, phut khlon, tha thon,</i>
<i>ya lut loi luan kluean duai Namo Buddhaya.</i>

102
00:11:27,920 --> 00:11:29,040
Let's go.

103
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,200
Water, Your Excellency.

104
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,120
Thank you.

105
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,400
I must thank all of you.

106
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,680
Had you not come to my aid,

107
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,120
my name would have ended today.

108
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:25,240
Those black-masked rebels,

109
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,360
they were the ones
who destroyed the railway,

110
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,440
weren't they?

111
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,640
No, sir.

112
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:33,040
I am

113
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,720
the leader of the black-masked rebels.

114
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:38,160
You're the rebel leader?

115
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,320
Had you not said so,
I would never have known.

116
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:46,040
Then if it wasn't you, who were they?

117
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:47,960
I recognized them.

118
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:51,360
They were Phraya Kaipetch's men, sir.

119
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:58,800
So that bastard Kaipetch
really meant to have me killed.

120
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,880
Ungrateful bastard.

121
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:06,000
The wickedness of Phraya Kaipetch
runs far deeper than this, sir.

122
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:09,200
Eh? You're Bandit Wad,

123
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:11,360
the man the authorities have been hunting,

124
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,600
aren't you?

125
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:13,760
Yes, sir.

126
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,960
I am Bandit Wad.

127
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,160
These are Yiwha

128
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:24,200
and Lasor, my children.

129
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,200
I was led to believe
that Bandit Wad and his children

130
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:30,240
were ruthless murderers,

131
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:32,520
like the rumors claimed.

132
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,600
My father robs the rich

133
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:37,360
who exploit others

134
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,440
and helps the oppressed poor.

135
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,880
The governor of Tha Khiri
fabricated those accusations

136
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,640
to eliminate us.

137
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,520
Tha Khiri is ruled by an evil man

138
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,400
who abuses his power unjustly.

139
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:54,160
We villagers have nowhere else to turn,

140
00:13:55,040 --> 00:13:57,120
except to you, Your Excellency.

141
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,160
What exactly has been happening here?

142
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:09,720
Sir, please.

143
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:23,200
Go fetch Luang Kamchat Phairi for me.

144
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,840
- Now.
- Yes, sir.

145
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:26,400
Go!

146
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,840
Chao Phraya Khongkhakhet…

147
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:03,160
Tha Khiri was once
a thriving frontier port.

148
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:07,400
How could it have become so lifeless?

149
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,160
The townspeople rose up
to drive out Phraya Kaipetch.

150
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:18,000
He unleashed black magic on them.

151
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:20,840
Many were injured and killed.

152
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,040
Others could no longer
endure his extortion

153
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:27,040
and fled to other lands.

154
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,560
That's why it looks like this now, sir.

155
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:33,280
And the local officials?

156
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:36,040
How could they allow the people

157
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:39,720
to suffer so terribly?

158
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,520
It is not so, sir.

159
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,560
Khun Yod Pakdee,

160
00:15:45,640 --> 00:15:46,840
my father,

161
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:51,360
was murdered along with our entire family
under mysterious circumstances years ago.

162
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,280
To this day,
the case has never received justice.

163
00:15:57,040 --> 00:15:59,720
You're Khun Yod Pakdee's son?

164
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:02,320
Yes, sir.

165
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,960
My name is Yiam.

166
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:09,640
I am the son of Khun Yod Pakdee,
Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

167
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:13,920
I have long heard
of Khun Yod Pakdee's reputation.

168
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,200
Never did I imagine

169
00:16:15,960 --> 00:16:18,040
such a tragic fate.

170
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,520
Very well, Yiam.

171
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,560
I will restore justice
for your father myself.

172
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:56,000
It has been years
since I last came to Tha Khiri.

173
00:16:57,200 --> 00:17:01,440
I never imagined
the city would fall so low.

174
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,720
Well, Tha Khiri

175
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:10,280
is plagued by criminals
on land and water alike, sir.

176
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:14,079
Suppressing them has been no easy task.
There have also been

177
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:18,000
endless rebel uprisings.

178
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:22,640
Even so,
I have never been negligent in my duties.

179
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:29,920
Then what do you say

180
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,440
about these documents?

181
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:43,680
They are forged documents,

182
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:47,440
fabricated by the rebels to frame me.

183
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:51,560
So the rebels can even forge

184
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:54,520
the governor's official seal,
can they, Kaipetch?

185
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:57,840
THE GOVERNOR AUTHORIZED THE OPERATION
OF OPIUM HOUSES AND GAMBLING DENS

186
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:03,520
And what of the murder of Khun Yod Pakdee?

187
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:07,480
How far has the case progressed,
Luang Kamchat Phairi?

188
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,200
Bandit Wad and his son Lasor

189
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:14,480
conspired to kill Khun Yod Pakdee, sir.

190
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,720
I did not kill Khun Yod, sir.

191
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:23,120
Pae, Bandit Pud's nephew,

192
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:27,160
gave a statement before he died
that you two were behind it.

193
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,240
That is not true, sir.

194
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,680
I investigated this case myself.

195
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,680
Bandit Pae never gave such testimony.

196
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:40,600
And do you have proof, Pun?

197
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,520
I do, sir.

198
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,760
Pae? You're not dead?

199
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:19,040
Hey.

200
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:20,800
Sit down.

201
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:33,960
There's an order to suspend your transfer
to the Provincial Patrol Department.

202
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:36,920
Phraya Kaipetch,

203
00:19:37,760 --> 00:19:40,280
the new governor,
will be the one to decide your case.

204
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,240
Phraya Kaipetch…

205
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:47,360
No. I'm not going.

206
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,320
If I go, he'll kill me for sure.

207
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,560
Why?

208
00:19:53,560 --> 00:19:55,000
Because this Phraya Kaipetch

209
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,920
is Duang's boss.

210
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,160
How do you know that?

211
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,840
I once overheard Uncle Pud

212
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,160
talking to Duang.

213
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,160
Phraya Kaipetch

214
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,880
was the one who ordered
Khun Yod Pakdee's murder.

215
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,160
Pun,

216
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:27,880
send me anywhere you want for questioning.

217
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:30,360
Just don't send me to him, please.

218
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:34,840
If I go,
he'll definitely kill me to silence me.

219
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,800
If you help me,

220
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:44,320
I swear I'll confess everything.

221
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,680
Please, Pun.

222
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:04,760
This will stop your heart

223
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,920
and make you pass out temporarily,
like you're dead.

224
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:14,800
Then I'll get you out myself.

225
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:29,280
If I hadn't used this method,

226
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:30,600
Pae,

227
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:34,200
the key witness
who knows what happened that night,

228
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:38,880
might've already been killed
by Phraya Kaipetch to silence him.

229
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:40,920
Pae,

230
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,480
what's the truth?

231
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:45,560
Tell me.

232
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:52,440
Uncle Pud and I were hired by Duang
to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

233
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:57,040
Uncle Pud set a trap,
using the Narai Transformation spell.

234
00:21:57,120 --> 00:22:01,040
<i>A wit su nu sa nu ti.</i>

235
00:22:01,760 --> 00:22:04,880
<i>He disguised himself as Bandit Wad</i>
<i>so Khun Yod would let his guard down.</i>

236
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:07,160
<i>Then he slaughtered</i>
<i>Khun Yod's entire family.</i>

237
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,880
You bandit.

238
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:15,680
In front of the High Commissioner,

239
00:22:16,360 --> 00:22:18,160
you still dare to lie?

240
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:21,200
If what you say is true,

241
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,720
where's your evidence?

242
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:32,280
Everyone who was there that night is dead.

243
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:35,120
The only one left is…

244
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:38,520
Lasor.

245
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:45,200
Is it true, Lasor?

246
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:49,920
Yes, sir.

247
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:54,560
I was fooled by Bandit Pud.
I was dragged into it

248
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:55,880
that night too.

249
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,800
I never wanted to kill Khun Yod Pakdee.

250
00:23:00,920 --> 00:23:04,360
I was under Bandit Pud's Saming spell.

251
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:08,680
So you killed Uncle Pud for revenge.

252
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,680
And he deserved it, didn't he?

253
00:23:12,960 --> 00:23:14,640
What about Phraya Decha,

254
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,080
the former governor?

255
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,680
Was his death your doing?

256
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:20,920
No, sir.

257
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:25,200
Then who killed him?

258
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,280
I don't know, sir.

259
00:23:27,360 --> 00:23:30,680
It was Phraya Kaipetch.
He killed Duang to silence him.

260
00:23:31,320 --> 00:23:32,440
Shut your mouth!

261
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:36,640
The day Phraya Decha died,
I was in the capital.

262
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:38,360
How could I have killed him?

263
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,400
With black magic,

264
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,960
just like you killed
the villagers at the market.

265
00:23:44,680 --> 00:23:45,840
You scumbag!

266
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:50,560
You…

267
00:23:57,840 --> 00:23:59,680
At Phraya Decha's corpse,

268
00:24:01,120 --> 00:24:03,160
we found feathers from a corpse-crow,

269
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:06,800
a mark of black sorcery, sir.

270
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:09,200
A corpse-crow?

271
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:12,200
That's a craft
used by black sorcerers, sir.

272
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:16,800
Phraya Kaipetch would know it very well.

273
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,680
What crow?

274
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,880
Don't slander me.
I know nothing about this.

275
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:31,640
Your Excellency,

276
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:33,160
I'm being framed.

277
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,960
Enough.

278
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,280
Whether it's true or not, we'll find out.

279
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:40,480
Take Kaipetch
to be interrogated by the tribunal.

280
00:25:01,080 --> 00:25:02,120
He got away.

281
00:25:07,040 --> 00:25:08,600
<i>Cha-lo maha cha-lo cha-lang maha cha-lang.</i>

282
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:11,160
<i>Cha-li-te maha cha-li-te</i>
<i>cha-li-tang maha cha-li-tang.</i>

283
00:25:22,840 --> 00:25:24,520
You're not going anywhere, Petch!

284
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:28,720
Wad, don't you let me get away.
I'll kill you for this!

285
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,440
Take him to jail.

286
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:34,520
I'm not going. I'm not going. I hate jail!

287
00:25:38,640 --> 00:25:40,840
Ai-ya! Who killed who?

288
00:25:40,920 --> 00:25:44,080
I don't know anything.

289
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,680
He's the one.

290
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:51,160
He worked with the governor. He ordered
both Chin Yuan and Chin Seng killed

291
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:53,160
so he could take everything,

292
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:55,520
monopolize trade in Tha Khiri

293
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:57,600
and become the sole tycoon.

294
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:59,000
Thongyoo,

295
00:26:00,520 --> 00:26:02,400
you really can't get enough.

296
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,520
You'd even kill your fellow Chinese men.

297
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:09,520
A crooked man like you

298
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:13,040
will only bring ruin.

299
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:15,400
Seize all his property

300
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:18,040
as assets of the realm.

301
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:23,200
Then take him to be punished
at the Provincial Patrol Department.

302
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:27,600
And you, Luang Kamchat Phairi.

303
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,800
You know right from wrong,

304
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:33,320
yet you turned a blind eye,

305
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:37,000
enabled scoundrels for personal gain,

306
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:39,200
and ignored the people's suffering.

307
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:43,160
I will strip you of your rank,
reduce you to a commoner,

308
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,400
exile you from Tha Khiri,

309
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,400
and appoint Pun

310
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,240
to take charge of the police
in your place.

311
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,280
Take him out.

312
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,800
Bandit Wad,

313
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:14,040
you and your son

314
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:17,400
have rendered great service
in helping me resolve these cases.

315
00:27:17,480 --> 00:27:20,440
But your crime
of gathering bandits still stands.

316
00:27:21,520 --> 00:27:23,480
I will submit a petition

317
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:25,600
for royal pardon

318
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,760
to clear the stain from you and your son.

319
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,040
It is a great blessing
to me and my son, sir.

320
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:41,440
Yiam,

321
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,320
I am proud, on Khun Yod's behalf,

322
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:47,120
to have a brave son like you.

323
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,960
Keep your virtue.

324
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,960
When I return, I will report your merits

325
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:56,360
and appoint you Khun Yod Phithak,

326
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,240
Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam,
just like your father.

327
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,280
It is the greatest honor
to my family, sir.

328
00:28:24,240 --> 00:28:27,800
Thank you
for helping me avoid the death penalty.

329
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:30,840
And I should thank you too

330
00:28:30,920 --> 00:28:32,480
for daring to tell the truth.

331
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,520
That's why every case
was finally resolved,

332
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:37,560
and the real criminals were punished.

333
00:28:41,040 --> 00:28:42,040
By the way,

334
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:47,600
you're not mad at me anymore?
About Chin Seng?

335
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:02,760
What's the point?

336
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:06,760
You've already been punished.

337
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,920
When I finish serving my time,

338
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:17,400
I'll apply to be
an informant for your unit.

339
00:29:18,600 --> 00:29:20,240
Don't underestimate me.

340
00:29:20,320 --> 00:29:23,960
I'm Pae the Ghost-Eared, alright.

341
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:28,480
By the time you get out,

342
00:29:29,240 --> 00:29:32,480
I'll probably be so old
I can't chase criminals anymore.

343
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:02,360
I'll hurry and send a new governor here,

344
00:30:03,280 --> 00:30:05,040
so the people have someone to rely on.

345
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,440
In the meantime, you and your people

346
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:11,200
keep watch and take good care of the town.

347
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,480
And what about Phraya Kaipetch, sir?

348
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:16,680
I'll take him to face punishment
at the tribunal court.

349
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:20,080
But he practices black sorcery.

350
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:23,560
It won't be easy to escort him.

351
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:27,520
Then we will break his spell

352
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,760
and cleanse his black magic

353
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:32,320
before handing him over to the tribunal.

354
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:35,240
Good. Thank you, Yiam.

355
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:43,680
I'll return again to inspect this place.

356
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,200
Rest in peace, Noree.

357
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,560
Don't worry about anything.

358
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:14,360
Ghost!

359
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:19,400
What ghost? It's me, Noree.

360
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,760
But you're dead.

361
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,920
You got fooled.

362
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:38,520
What the hell were you thinking, Pun?

363
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:40,400
Yeah.

364
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:46,200
Pun was afraid I'd get hurt,
so he made it look like I died,

365
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:49,160
so I wouldn't become
their bargaining chip.

366
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:52,320
That way, he could investigate
the residence more easily.

367
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:57,120
Pun,

368
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:58,840
you're really a schemer.

369
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:00,880
You're better at tricking people
than a ghost.

370
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:04,160
Oh? How else would I be a policeman?

371
00:32:11,400 --> 00:32:13,240
Now that the bad times are over,

372
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:16,720
when's the auspicious day, Pun?

373
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:21,200
An auspicious day for what?

374
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:34,600
Noree…

375
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:40,880
Be my wife, Noree.

376
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:31,520
It's late.
The dew's heavy. You'll get sick.

377
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:43,920
Do you remember this bracelet?

378
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,560
Of course.

379
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:51,360
The human-faced bead bracelet.

380
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:56,000
I bought it as a stand-in for me.

381
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,960
I thought you'd thrown it away.

382
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,200
I…

383
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:06,480
could never throw away
something you gave me.

384
00:34:11,719 --> 00:34:13,000
Look.

385
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,840
This is the only thing
that's always smiling at me.

386
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:27,040
From now on,

387
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:30,159
I'll be the one smiling at you.

388
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,199
- Yiam.
- Hm?

389
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:46,840
What if someone sees?

390
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,120
No one will.

391
00:35:00,760 --> 00:35:01,840
Dad.

392
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:27,160
Tomorrow, I'll hold
the wrist-tying ceremony for you two

393
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,240
so you won't become
the townspeople's gossip.

394
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,320
Isn't that too soon, Dad?

395
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:39,000
Yiwha and I
haven't even had time to prepare.

396
00:35:39,080 --> 00:35:41,720
You two have already slept together
as husband and wife.

397
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:45,600
What else is there to prepare?

398
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:58,520
Actually,

399
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:01,560
your father Yod and I

400
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:04,360
made an agreement long ago

401
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:08,720
to unite you two as husband and wife.

402
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:13,240
But we never performed
the proper ceremony.

403
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,440
If you're husband and wife,

404
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:18,200
it must be done according to tradition.

405
00:36:18,920 --> 00:36:20,280
Only then can I finally rest easy.

406
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:24,720
But why does it have to be tomorrow?

407
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:27,360
Can't it be another day?

408
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:33,320
Lasor will have
his memories erased tomorrow night.

409
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:37,560
I want him to have a good moment

410
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:41,200
before he can't remember
anything ever again.

411
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,120
Alright.

412
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:58,400
I want Lasor

413
00:36:59,160 --> 00:37:01,560
to be there on an important day
for me and Yiam too.

414
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:21,520
Nui,

415
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:25,640
I have to release your spirit
so you can be reborn

416
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:27,960
before

417
00:37:29,920 --> 00:37:31,320
Dad erases my memories.

418
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:36,320
I'll be born as your brother again.

419
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:28,360
Goodbye, Nui.

420
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:57,880
Remember this.

421
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:01,480
My blood flows within you.

422
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:03,640
Never betray me.

423
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:08,920
Otherwise,
you'll learn of something more terrifying

424
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:09,880
than death.

425
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:16,200
I'm not losing to you that easily, Wad.

426
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,600
<i>Lasor.</i>

427
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,240
<i>Lasor.</i>

428
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:32,120
<i>Lasor.</i>

429
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:35,440
<i>Lasor.</i>

430
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,600
<i>Lasor.</i>

431
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:43,240
I won't be your tool anymore, Kaipetch!

432
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:49,640
Let's see

433
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:52,920
how much longer you can endure it.

434
00:40:17,280 --> 00:40:20,320
I found a motorboat
to send Lasor to Lanka.

435
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,040
So tomorrow…

436
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:29,400
I'll be losing one of my children.

437
00:40:35,600 --> 00:40:37,400
No one stays with us forever.

438
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:41,320
One day, we all must part,

439
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,040
whether it's parting while alive

440
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:46,320
or parting by death.

441
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:51,360
It's only about
which kind of parting hurts more.

442
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:15,040
If your mother were still alive,
she'd be so happy

443
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:19,560
to see you two lying on my lap like this.

444
00:41:22,520 --> 00:41:25,320
Do you remember when we were kids, Lasor?

445
00:41:25,400 --> 00:41:27,120
Back in Chum Suea.

446
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:31,800
Life was hard, but we were happy.

447
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,520
If I could turn back time,

448
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:41,840
I wouldn't mess things up.

449
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:45,600
I'd listen to you.

450
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:50,880
Do you know

451
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:55,360
why your mother named you
"Yiwha" and "Lasor"?

452
00:41:56,440 --> 00:41:57,600
Why, Dad?

453
00:42:00,840 --> 00:42:02,640
The elders say

454
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:06,400
with twins, the one born first

455
00:42:06,480 --> 00:42:08,680
is the younger one.

456
00:42:08,760 --> 00:42:11,640
And the one born after is the eldest.

457
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,320
Because the older sibling

458
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:18,760
sacrifices so the younger
can open their eyes to the world first.

459
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:21,000
So this one

460
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:22,400
has to be the eldest,

461
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:24,720
and that one

462
00:42:26,760 --> 00:42:28,160
has to be younger.

463
00:42:30,720 --> 00:42:33,400
We still haven't named them.

464
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,320
What should we call them?

465
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:40,040
Theng? Nui?

466
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,880
Iad? Kaew?

467
00:42:45,840 --> 00:42:47,480
Or Samor?

468
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:49,400
No.

469
00:42:50,560 --> 00:42:52,640
Those sound like shadow-puppet names.

470
00:42:57,280 --> 00:42:58,640
For our daughter,

471
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:03,080
I want to name her Yiwha,

472
00:43:03,600 --> 00:43:05,000
meaning "heart."

473
00:43:06,880 --> 00:43:11,720
Because she's the apple of our eye,
our heart.

474
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:15,200
Yiwha.

475
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:17,800
That's a beautiful name.

476
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:21,440
Then what about our son?

477
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:24,040
Back in my hometown,

478
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:27,680
we call jasmine "Malasor"

479
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:31,840
How about "Lasor"?

480
00:43:33,920 --> 00:43:35,760
What kind of man is named after jasmine?

481
00:43:38,840 --> 00:43:42,560
Jasmine is used to string garlands
to worship the Buddha.

482
00:43:43,560 --> 00:43:47,320
So he'll grow up to be a good person,
living with virtue and morality.

483
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:53,200
Then when he grows up,

484
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:55,240
maybe he'll become an abbot.

485
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:57,440
Come on…

486
00:43:59,880 --> 00:44:01,360
Lasor it is.

487
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:11,960
Mom must've been so heartbroken

488
00:44:14,040 --> 00:44:16,360
having a rotten child like me.

489
00:44:20,680 --> 00:44:23,600
Everyone makes mistakes.

490
00:44:23,680 --> 00:44:27,320
But you made one, and you changed.

491
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:30,360
Mom would be proud of you.

492
00:45:07,040 --> 00:45:08,360
I'm sorry, Dad,

493
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:12,720
that I couldn't be a good son.

494
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:18,200
Now that you've realized it, I'm glad.

495
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:35,480
No matter what,
you'll always be the best brother to me.

496
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:41,200
I'm so lucky, Yiwha,

497
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,440
to have a sister like you.

498
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:00,920
Tomorrow night, at the second watch,

499
00:46:04,160 --> 00:46:06,480
I'll cleanse the black sorcery from you

500
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:10,880
and erase every memory you've ever had.

501
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:13,320
And the next day,

502
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:18,720
I'll ordain you,
so you can become a new Lasor.

503
00:46:21,320 --> 00:46:23,760
May you stay firm in virtue and morality,

504
00:46:23,840 --> 00:46:26,280
just as your mother always wished.

505
00:46:28,400 --> 00:46:31,440
Can you do this
for your mom and me one last time?

506
00:46:36,560 --> 00:46:37,560
Yes, Dad.

507
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:41,560
I can do it.

508
00:48:06,760 --> 00:48:08,480
You're more beautiful than any other day.

509
00:48:11,560 --> 00:48:12,400
So…

510
00:48:13,480 --> 00:48:15,320
I'm not beautiful on other days?

511
00:48:18,960 --> 00:48:21,160
On other days,
you're beautiful as the one I love.

512
00:48:23,440 --> 00:48:24,440
But today,

513
00:48:28,520 --> 00:48:30,280
you're beautiful as my bride.

514
00:48:44,240 --> 00:48:45,480
At last,

515
00:48:45,560 --> 00:48:47,480
the day I've been waiting for is here.

516
00:48:50,200 --> 00:48:51,640
What have you been waiting for?

517
00:48:52,880 --> 00:48:54,680
The day we could be together,

518
00:48:57,560 --> 00:49:00,880
the day we share a pillow,
truly as husband and wife.

519
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:05,400
Thank you

520
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:07,680
for waiting for me.

521
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:13,880
Thank you for enduring everything for me,

522
00:49:15,880 --> 00:49:18,760
and for guiding me back
to being your Blur again.

523
00:49:21,440 --> 00:49:23,280
And I should thank you too

524
00:49:24,400 --> 00:49:27,000
for returning to the same Orror.

525
00:49:54,080 --> 00:49:56,200
You'll always be my Orror.

526
00:49:57,840 --> 00:49:59,080
This Blur

527
00:50:01,120 --> 00:50:03,560
gives his whole heart to you alone.

528
00:50:05,320 --> 00:50:07,120
No matter what happens,

529
00:50:08,400 --> 00:50:10,840
in happiness or in suffering,

530
00:50:13,160 --> 00:50:14,720
I'll stay by your side,

531
00:50:19,200 --> 00:50:20,160
love you,

532
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:23,440
and take care of you forever.

533
00:51:21,360 --> 00:51:22,200
Come on.

534
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:28,040
May you two

535
00:51:29,040 --> 00:51:30,640
stay together

536
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:34,600
and grow old together.

537
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:38,480
May you love

538
00:51:38,560 --> 00:51:41,080
and take care of each other
until you're gray and wrinkled.

539
00:51:41,680 --> 00:51:43,400
If one of you is fire,

540
00:51:44,680 --> 00:51:46,600
let the other be water.

541
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:49,840
Give and take. Rely on each other.

542
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:54,440
And when times are hard,
forgive one another.

543
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:00,200
Alright.

544
00:52:06,080 --> 00:52:07,000
Lasor.

545
00:52:09,840 --> 00:52:11,560
Come bless your sister.

546
00:52:25,560 --> 00:52:27,120
I wish you

547
00:52:28,840 --> 00:52:30,440
a good life partner

548
00:52:31,960 --> 00:52:33,000
and a good life.

549
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:39,240
Don't fall as low as I did.

550
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:42,320
Lasor…

551
00:52:48,800 --> 00:52:49,680
Yiam,

552
00:52:51,640 --> 00:52:53,880
I'm entrusting my little sister to you.

553
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:55,160
I promise.

554
00:52:57,440 --> 00:52:59,400
I'll protect Yiwha with my life.

555
00:53:01,280 --> 00:53:02,640
Don't worry.

556
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:29,720
What's wrong, Chang?

557
00:53:35,360 --> 00:53:36,920
I miss Talong.

558
00:53:46,560 --> 00:53:48,960
Come on.

559
00:53:49,600 --> 00:53:51,480
Talong is at peace now.

560
00:53:52,080 --> 00:53:55,040
If he weren't,
he would've come back already.

561
00:53:55,120 --> 00:53:57,240
- Right, Noree?
- Pun!

562
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:08,520
Even if Talong's body
is no longer with you,

563
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:11,560
I believe he hasn't gone anywhere.

564
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:15,760
He's still right beside you.

565
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:19,240
And he'll always live in your heart.

566
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:11,120
<i>I know you're still with me, Talong.</i>

567
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:38,920
Ugh! My stomach. Help.

568
00:55:39,600 --> 00:55:40,840
My stomach hurts.

569
00:55:50,960 --> 00:55:51,840
Idiot.

570
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:22,320
<i>Remember this.</i>

571
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:26,680
<i>My blood flows within you.</i>

572
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:29,920
<i>Never betray me.</i>

573
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:31,200
<i>Otherwise,</i>

574
00:56:31,800 --> 00:56:35,360
<i>you'll learn of something more terrifying</i>

575
00:56:35,440 --> 00:56:36,760
<i>than death.</i>

576
00:56:41,560 --> 00:56:43,400
Wad! Wad!

577
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:48,280
Petch cast a sorcery centipede on you.

578
00:56:49,560 --> 00:56:53,080
Because you're still useful to me, Lasor.

579
00:56:54,200 --> 00:56:55,040
What are you going to--

580
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:58,360
I saved you so many times.

581
00:56:58,440 --> 00:57:01,160
Now it's time you repay me.

582
00:57:01,240 --> 00:57:03,800
<i>Didn't you promise</i>
<i>you'd cleanse the spell and ordain?</i>

583
00:57:03,880 --> 00:57:05,720
<i>Why did you suddenly</i>
<i>lash out and kill Kaipetch?</i>

584
00:57:05,800 --> 00:57:09,960
Petch just died,
why is his skin rotting so fast?

585
00:57:10,040 --> 00:57:11,560
You have to help me.

586
00:57:12,440 --> 00:57:14,200
How am I supposed to help you?

587
00:57:16,440 --> 00:57:18,600
My brother is acting strange.

588
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:20,320
Stop overthinking.

589
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:22,840
Get ready to go back
to Khuan Phra-ngam with me.

590
00:57:22,920 --> 00:57:23,880
How much time do we have left?

591
00:57:23,960 --> 00:57:26,480
In three nights,
there will be a lunar eclipse.

592
00:58:10,520 --> 00:58:12,840
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
